---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Deutsch Lernen"
	description="Our mission is to make learning German accessible, structured, and enjoyable for everyone."
	pubDate={new Date('June 29 2026')}
>
	<h2>Our Mission</h2>
	<p>
		Deutsch Lernen was built with one goal in mind: to make learning German as accessible,
		structured, and enjoyable as possible — whether you are starting from zero or pushing toward
		fluency.
	</p>
	<p>
		German is one of the most spoken languages in Europe and opens doors to study, work, and life
		in Germany, Austria, and Switzerland. Yet finding a single place that covers vocabulary,
		grammar, reading, and progress tracking — without switching between five different apps — has
		always been harder than it should be. That is the gap we set out to close.
	</p>

	<h2>What We Offer</h2>
	<p>
		The platform is organized around four core learning modules, designed to work together and
		cover all levels from A1 to C1:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Vocabulary</strong> — Structured word lists organized by level and topic, so you
			always know what to learn next.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Grammar Exercises</strong> — Interactive exercises covering cases, verb
			conjugations, sentence structure, and the details that make German click.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Reading Stories</strong> — Short stories graded by difficulty, with audio support,
			so you practice comprehension at the right level.
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Progress Tracking</strong> — Streaks, completed lessons, time spent, and a
			leaderboard to keep you motivated day after day.
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>For Learners and Teachers</h2>
	<p>
		Deutsch Lernen works for individual learners who study on their own schedule, and for teachers
		who want to assign exercises, follow their students' progress, and manage a class from a single
		dashboard. Sign in takes one click with your Google account — no passwords to manage.
	</p>

	<h2>The Blog</h2>
	<p>
		Alongside the app, we publish articles in English, French, and Arabic covering learning
		strategies, grammar tips, vocabulary guides, and resources to help you get the most out of your
		German journey. Browse the <a href="/blog">blog</a> to find content in your language.
	</p>
</Layout>
